        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 9:29PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 928 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Julian, or near Madison, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Danville, Seth, Madison, Foster, Woodville, Ashford, Alkol, Racine,
Julian, and Chesapeake.

This includes the following highways...
West Virginia Turnpike between mile markers 86 and 87.
Route 119 between mile markers 49 and 60.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM EDT for
central West Virginia.</instruction>
